This paper is about machine translation, which falls under the category of computational linguistics. The paper specifically focuses on transliteration, which is a sub-field of machine translation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses neural networks, which falls under the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with out-of-vocabulary words, which is a problem in information retrieval, falling under the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with low-resource languages, which is a problem in natural language processing, falling under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
